============================================================
PART 5: Exhaustive n=5 analysis - what does regularity force?
============================================================
  At n=5: disj3 = 0 always (need 6 vertices for disjoint pair)
  So K = c5 - 2*ov1 - 2*ov2 = c5 - 2*(ov1+ov2) = c5 - 2*C(c3,2)
  For regular: c3 = 5 = 5, C(c3,2) = 10
  K = c5 - 20
  Directed 5-cycles in regular n=5: [2]
  Verification: K = c5 - 20 = 2 - 20 = -18

