============================================================
PART 9: Algebraic identity behind constancy
============================================================
  For regular n=7, computing lambda_{ij} = |out(j) cap in(i)| for edge i->j:
    Lambda distribution: {2: 21}
    DRT lambda = (n-3)/4 = 1.0
    DRT ov2 = n*m*C(lambda,2) = 0.0
    Actual ov2 for Paley (which IS doubly regular): 21

  Check: for Paley T_7, lambda = 1 means each edge is in exactly 1 three-cycle
  So C(1,2) = 0, meaning no two 3-cycles share an edge!
  This means ov2 = 0 for doubly regular n=7.
  Actual ov2 = 21

  Lambda distributions for non-Paley regular n=7:
